recommend keep-going -- --private-home is built, self-tested for correctness (deny counts, exclusion logic, write-fence preservation) from inside this window as far as this window can honestly test, and needs one outside-the-jail witness run from Keaton to fully close the loop, same as --harden-home before it. The named symlink-resolution gap is a real, separate follow-up, not urgent. After that, the longest-standing open thread returns to the Neth ladder's two-posture root install.
